{"id": "27870", "post": "<div class=\"post-27870 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-editorial tag-amazon tag-amazon-aws tag-aws tag-cloud-hosting tag-cloudflare tag-network\" id=\"post-27870\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/cloudflare-complains-about-amazon-aws-egress-fees/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Cloudflare Complains About Amazon AWS Egress Fees</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" alt=\"Tags: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/amazon/\" rel=\"tag\">amazon</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/amazon-aws/\" rel=\"tag\">amazon aws</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/aws/\" rel=\"tag\">aws</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/cloud-hosting/\" rel=\"tag\">cloud hosting</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/cloudflare/\" rel=\"tag\">cloudflare</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/network/\" rel=\"tag\">network</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" alt=\"Date/Time: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> July 28, 2021 @ 12:00 pm, by raindog308</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/cloudflare.png\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-27871 litespeed-loaded\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/cloudflare.png\" alt=\"cloudflare logo\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" align=\"right\" hspace=\"20\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/cloudflare.png 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/cloudflare-150x150.png 150w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/cloudflare.png 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/cloudflare-150x150.png 150w\" data-was-processed=\"true\">In a <a href=\"https://blog.cloudflare.com/aws-egregious-egress\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"Cloudflare Blog\">blog post this week</a>, Cloudflare complained that Amazon AWS\u2019s egress fees are too high.&nbsp; According to CF\u2019s calculations, customers are paying:</p><ul><li>80 times Amazon\u2019s costs in the US, Canada, and Europe</li><li>21 times Amazon\u2019s costs in South America</li><li>Between 3.5 times and 17 times Amazon\u2019s costs in Asia</li></ul><p>As they put it, \u201cAmazon stands alone in not passing on savings\u201d and notes that Amazon AWS has declined to be part of the <a href=\"https://www.cloudflare.com/bandwidth-alliance/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"bandwidth alliance\">Bandwidth Alliance</a>, in which major providers substantially discount egress charges between mutual Cloudflare customers.</p><p>Industry-wide, over the last 10 years, wholesale bandwidth costs are 93% cheaper than they were in 2011.&nbsp; However, Amazon AWS\u2019s costs is only 25% cheaper.</p><p>There\u2019s a lot more analysis in the post, which is a very interesting read and emphasizes the point that big cloud players are not the right fit for all users. Paying per-gigabyte for network traffic is enormously expensive and in many cases, buying a VM package with bundled bandwidth is more cost-effective.</p><div class=\"relpost-thumb-wrapper\"><div class=\"relpost-thumb-container\"><h3>Related posts:</h3><div style=\"clear: both\"></div><div style=\"clear: both\"></div><div class=\"relpost-block-container\"><a class=\"relpost-block-single\" href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/rackspace-lays-off-10-of-its-workforce/\"><div class=\"relpost-custom-block-single\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 215px;\"><div class=\"relpost-block-single-image\" alt=\"